places.name: Aeropuerto Internacional de Nadi
places.perex: El Aeropuerto internacional de Nadi? es la entrada internacional principal para las islas Fiyi.

places.name: Sri Siva Subramaniya Temple
places.perex: The Sri Siva Subramaniya temple is a Hindu temple in Nadi, Fiji. It is at the southern end of the main road through Nadi.

places.name: Nausori International Airport
places.perex: Nausori International Airport. Also known as Luvuluvu, Nausori Airport is the second international airport in Fiji.

places.name: Garden of the Sleeping Giant
places.perex: With more than 2,000 kinds of orchids, this wonderful garden is a perfect place for a peaceful stroll. This place will take your breath away.

places.name: Denarau Marina
places.perex: Sit at one of the marina's restaurants and watch the yachts. This place also offers some excellent shopping opportunities.

places.name: Museo de Fiyi
places.perex: El Museo de Fiyi​ es un museo en Suva, en los jardines botánicos situado en la ciudad capital, los Jardines Thurston.

places.name: Navala Village
places.perex: Navala is a village in the Ba Highlands of northern-central Viti Levu, Fiji. It is noted for its thatched buildings, amounting to over 200.

places.name: Horseshoe Bay
places.perex: On of the finest beaches in Fiji. This half-moon pictoreque beach was created by an extinct volcano whose crater fell away on one side.

places.name: Aeropuerto de Rotuma
places.perex: El Aeropuerto de Rotuma​ es un aeropuerto al servicio de la isla de Rotuma​ una de las que conforma el archipiélago y nación de Fiyi.​​ Se…

places.name: Kadavu (KDV)
places.perex: Vunisea Airport is an airport located near Vunisea on Kadavu Island in Fiji.

places.name: Lakeba Island Airport
places.perex: Lakeba Airport is an airport in Lakeba, one of the Lau Islands in southern Fiji. It is operated by Airports Fiji Limited.

places.name: Cicia Airport
places.perex: Cicia Airport is an airport serving Cicia, one of the Lau Islands in the Eastern Division of Fiji. It is operated by Airports Fiji Limited.

places.name: Sabeto Hot Springs and Mud Pool
places.perex: Also known as the Sabeto Mud Baths, this stinky area provides a unique opportunity to take a dip into 3 warm mud pools. Who could resist?

places.name: Tawuni Hill Fort
places.perex: Learn about the history of cannibalism, daily life, and warfare between Fiji and Tonga in this village in a beautiful setting.

places.name: Sigadoka Sand Dunes
places.perex: This wonder covers the area of 650ha and is significant for its archaeological history and  diverse mixture of plant and bird species.

places.name: Kula Eco Park
places.perex: An award winning ecological preserve on Viti Levu and a popular tourist attraction focusing on the preservation of Fiji's fauna and flora.

places.name: Natadola Beach
places.perex: One of the best beaches in Fiji with pure white sand and turquoise shallow water. Great for swimming, surfing and horse riding.

places.name: Pacific Harbour Arts Village
places.perex: This resort offers a variety of activities, services, and a good introduction to Fijian culture. The place to go for souvenir hunting.

places.name: Udre Udre
places.perex: Ratru Udre Udre fue un jefe fiyiano conocido por ser considerado como el más prolífico caníbal de la humanidad, y una de las últimas…

places.name: Monte Tomanivi
places.perex: Monte Tomanivi es la más alta montaña de Fiyi. Se encuentra en la isla de Viti Levu y pertenece a la cadena que divide de norte a sur la…

places.name: Suva Municipal Market
places.perex: Hungry? Then look around this market, enjoy the friendly atmosphere and buy fresh local produce at great prices.

places.name: Jardines Thurston
places.perex: Los Jardines Thurston​ es el nombre que reciben los jardines botánicos de Fiyi.

places.name: ZIP Fiji
places.perex: Soar through the jungle from one tree to another and enjoy the thrill. A must-do experience for all age groups.

places.name: Vuaqava
places.perex: Vuaqava is an outlier to Kabara, 5 kilometers to the SSW, in Fiji's Southern Lau Group. It occupies an area of 8.1 km2.

places.name: Coral Coast Railway
places.perex: Hop on the open-air train and enjoy the scenery as you ride past local communities and thick vegetation at staggering 20 km/h speed.

places.name: Sheraton Denerau Golf and Racquet Club
places.perex: Pictoresque and rather challenging golf course with water and bunkers in the shape of marine creatures.

places.name: Natadola Bay Championship Golf Course
places.perex: This is one of the most spectacular golf courses you can come across. Fairly challenging, stunning views and fantastic location.

places.name: Bouma National Heritage Park
places.perex: Hike to 3 Tavoro waterfalls in the lush rainforest, take pictures of the stunning views on the way there and go for a refreshing swim.

places.name: KoroSun Dive
places.perex: Fancy some diving adventure? This company will show you marine life of Fiji, such as soft corals, hammer head sharks and colourful fish.

places.name: Kila World
places.perex: This park offers exciting attractions for adrenaline junkies. Try your limits on ropes courses ranging from low ropes to the Giant Swing.

places.name: Colo-I-Suva Forest Park
places.perex: This is a lovely lush rainforest renowned for its tropical flora and birds, offering hiking trails and swimming. Take your wellies!

places.name: Waitabu Marine Park
places.perex: Pay a small fee and snorkel the community protected coral reef. You will see various colorful fish, reef sharks, nudibranchs and many more.

places.name: The Salad Bowl Cave Tour
places.perex: This trip will take you to many interesting places. Visit the NAIHEHE cave, ride on a bamboo raft, and see a genuine Fijian village.

places.name: Lavena Coastal Walk
places.perex: Take a guided tour and spend a few hours enjoying the breathtaking views of the tropical forest and black sand beaches.

places.name: Church of Saint Francis Xavier
places.perex: European style stone church with interesting murals serving the needs of around 2000 Catholics from the surrounding area.

J. Hunter Pearl Farm
places.perex: If you are looking for the perfect souvenir, visit Justin Hunter's pearl farm where he and his team cultivate uniquely coloured pearls.

places.name: Bebe Spa
places.perex: Treat yourself to one of divine treatments in this lovely spa. Fancy a traditional Fijian massage?

places.name: Heavenly Spa by Westin
places.perex: Feeling sore from lying on the beach? Never mind. This spa will spoil you rotten.

places.name: Sea Trek Fiji
places.perex: An out-of-this-world experience...almost literally. If you've ever wondered what it's like to walk on the Moon, this is it.

places.name: Bula Massage Clinic
places.perex: This place is heaven. Not just one but three masseurs will be taking care of your body at the same time in this highly recommended spa.

places.name: Vatukarasa Village
places.perex: Visit this traditional village and have a chat with more than friendly villagers about their lifestyle and interesting social schemes.

places.name: Malt House Brewery and Restaurant
places.perex: This is a popular restaurant with a lively atmosphere serving international and local cuisine as well as some of the best beer.
